Description: Renaissance Weekends build bridges among innovative leaders of all ages, with exceptionally diverse perspectives.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Renaissance Weekends build bridges among innovative leaders of all ages, with exceptionally diverse perspectives. For more than 30 years, Renaissance Weekends® — inter-generational, inter-disciplinary, invitation-only retreats — have celebrated both ideas & relationships. Civility prevails; partisanship is frowned upon; commercialism, banned.  Renaissance Weekends were conceived in 1981, when friends were lamenting that, despite meeting fascinating people in their work and everyday lives, they rarely had occasion to learn from each other in a personal and substantive way. To that end, 60 families pioneered Ambassador and Mrs. Lader's four-day New Year's "house party."  Over the decades, the New Year's gathering has retained the same spirit and has become a "reunion" of some 1,000+ past participants and remarkable newcomers. Smaller Weekends, around other holidays and vacation times, have much the same character as the original gathering.  Renaissance Weekend's 25th Anniversary — co-chaired by past participants Presidents Gerald Ford and Bill Clinton — was celebrated at gatherings throughout 2006. The 2014 Weekends - celebrating the 100th Renaissance Weekend and launching the next 100 - will include reunions of participants from the 30+ years' past Weekends.  Scores of Nobel laureates, Pulitzer, MacArthur and Templeton Prize-winners, dozens of Oscar-, Emmy- and Grammy-winners, Supreme Court Justices, Senators, Congressmen and Governors, many astronauts, 16 former candidates for U.S. President (Republicans and Democrats), and Wimbledon and Olympic champions, as well as professional athletes, have regularly been among the distinguished participants.  But everyone who comes to Renaissance Weekend has a noteworthy and often inspiring story to tell. For many, their most consequential achievements and contributions are ahead. For some, Renaissance's ideas and relationships play an important part in their professional and personal development.  The result has been a cross-generational "continuing conversation" of accomplished individuals with broadly divergent perspectives and no political agenda. Yet the Weekends' legacy of ideas and friendships has fostered significant projects, ventures and public service.
Industry Groups: Events, Media and Entertainment, Other, Social Impact

Description: We are a local commerce and social engagement company offering great specials from locally owned and operated businesses.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We are passionate about using technology to transform the way small businesses, especially restaurants, transact their business. We believe fervently in the notion that there is a better way and technology is a tool that needs to be used a lot more than it is being used presently. We focus on the small restaurants because they need the most help but we do not limit ourselves by any notion of exclusivity. For us finding a better way to connect restaurants to customers is what gets us out of bed in the morning. Some of these restaurants will be big and established, many will be small and needy. We will add value to both keeping in mind that we need to give our end users the best possible experience when they come to our site.  We are a small company ourselves but have never let that stand in the way of doing the big things that we believe in. This has helped us jump many a hurdle and while many others have fallen by the wayside we continue to find a way to keep going. Perseverance is a hallmark of our small team. Adaptability is something we consider important. We remind ourselves everyday that we must find a way.  For our restaurant partners, we will be your ally and we will continue to look for ways in which we can make it easier for you to get discovered, to succeed in ecommerce and to save on costs. For our consumers we will strive to give the best possible experience – better than anything that might be out there – and the best possible value, recognizing that while there are some commonalities among end users, we must go beyond what is common in order to be able to personalize the experience to each individual.
Industry Groups: Apps, Commerce and Shopping, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Software
